==Polish==
===Etymology===
From a [[Polish]] word meaning "[[stroke]]"
===Noun===
'''kreska''' (diminutive: [[kreseczka]])

# {{orthography}}: a [[diacritic]] closely resembling an [[acute accent]].

===Usage===
The ''kreska'' is used in Polish writing to indicate consonants that have been "softened" ([[palatalized]]). It therefore appears only over consonants.

